crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: The binary is a malicious trojan. It dynamically resolves a large number of sensitive Windows APIs at runtime to obscure its functionality. It contains functions for HTTP communication using WinINet, indicating command and control (C2) capabilities. Concrete IOCs include the C2 URI paths `host/img/jpg/post.php` for data exfiltration and `host/img/jpg/download.php` for downloading additional payloads. It also has capabilities to enumerate processes (`CreateToolhelp32Snapshot`), read process memory (`ReadProcessMemory`), and manipulate files and the registry, which are typical behaviors for information stealers and backdoors.
